18:03.880 --> 18:11.940
This is David Carson. And Daryl Lane. Bob Wayne owns a specialty bookstore in
Fort Worth, Texas called Fantastic Worlds. He sells almost anything related to

18:11.940 --> 18:18.840
science fiction or fantasy, including comics, gaming paraphernalia, and video
material. He is also a collector, principally of comics and hardback science

18:18.840 --> 18:26.100
fiction books. We spoke with him recently about his hardback collection. Just
asking questions a curious non-collector might think of. What, for instance,

18:26.260 --> 18:36.660
does he consider the ultimate for a hardback collector of science fiction? Well,
among the ultimate items to find in the hardcover field are some of the double

18:36.660 --> 18:48.340
-day hardcover books of recent years that had very small printings and, for one
reason or another, had very small distribution. Two that come to mind are Roger

18:48.340 --> 19:01.480
Zelazny's Nine Princes in Amber and Philip Jose Farmer's Flesh. And I would
be in the position of passing apocryphal, potentially, stories about why these

19:01.480 --> 19:11.680
books are in slow editions or small editions. But my understanding is that both
of these books were remaindered very quickly upon publication and had very

19:11.680 --> 19:27.180
little distribution outside of review copies and library copies. So those books
are both hard to find. I've only seen two copies of either of those books in the

19:27.180 --> 19:36.900
time that I've been collecting books and looking at hardcovers. It's about 69.
We also asked him if he ever made any accidental finds, any nuggets that he

19:36.900 --> 19:47.740
hadn't been expecting. I've had a number of strokes of what I would have to
consider luck as far as finding books that I consider to be quite valuable. I

19:47.740 --> 19:58.580
was at a book fair at one time with Louis Shiner, a short story writer who's
appeared in Omni and Cheyall and various magazines. And we were just looking

19:58.580 --> 20:09.540
through tons and tons of hardcover books, miles and miles of historical
romances. And we were giving up. And over in a little bitty pile on the side,

20:09.640 --> 20:18.380
there was a little bitty book. A little bit was sticking out. It looked
familiar. And it was a Gnome Press book written by Henry Kuttner under the name

20:18.380 --> 20:28.640
of Louis Paget called Robots Have No Tails that was in perfect condition. And
they had priced it at what I thought was the outrageous price of 40 cents. But I

20:28.640 --> 20:40.320
went on ahead and paid the 40 cents. That was a tough blow to pay that much
money for a book worth just, you know, 100, 200 times more than that. But I was

20:40.320 --> 20:51.520
able to tear loose the money. We wondered if there was any part of his
collection he's most proud of. I would have to say that there's not really any

20:51.520 --> 21:07.800
one item that I'm most proud of as far as being difficult to find. And I do have
a one-of-a-kind item in my collection that I purchased at an auction this last

21:07.800 --> 21:20.220
summer. It's a translation from the French of the book, Philip Jose Farmer
Conquers the Universe, that Philip Jose Farmer donated to an auction at a

21:20.220 --> 21:28.060
convention that my store sponsored in Dallas during the summer. And that has a
cover letter and it's signed by Philip Jose Farmer and a copy of the book in

21:28.060 --> 21:35.900
French that it was translated from. And it's a translation that the publisher
who has the option on this book, Berkley Books, has decided that they did not

21:35.900 --> 21:46.780
want to publish in that form. So that will be the only version of that in
English. So I suppose as far as a rarity, having the only copy floating around

21:46.780 --> 21:55.600
of that should be a novelty to some extent. Collecting in the science fiction
field is becoming a popular hobby among science fiction and fantasy fans. Fans

21:55.600 --> 22:03.500
will collect anything, too. Books, magazines, comics, movie memorabilia,
artwork, and so on. If you're interested, Bob Wayne can help you out with advice

22:03.500 --> 22:07.200
or material. Just contact the Fantastic Worlds Bookstore in Fort Worth, Texas.

